synopsis:       libcurl bindings
description:
  This package provides a Haskell bindings to libcurl. It is basically a 1:1
  mapping of libcurl's C API (please see <http://curl.haxx.se/libcurl/>).
  .
  libcurl is a free and easy-to-use client-side URL transfer library,
  supporting DICT, FILE, FTP, FTPS, GOPHER, HTTP, HTTPS, IMAP, IMAPS, LDAP,
  LDAPS, POP3, POP3S, RTMP, RTSP, SCP, SFTP, SMTP, SMTPS, TELNET and TFTP.
  libcurl supports SSL certificates, HTTP POST, HTTP PUT, FTP uploading, HTTP
  form based upload, proxies, cookies, user+password authentication (Basic,
  Digest, NTLM, Negotiate, Kerberos), file transfer resume, http proxy
  tunneling and more!
  .
  libcurl is highly portable, it builds and works identically on numerous
  platforms, including Solaris, NetBSD, FreeBSD, OpenBSD, Darwin, HPUX, IRIX,
  AIX, Tru64, Linux, UnixWare, HURD, Windows, Amiga, OS/2, BeOs, Mac OS X,
  Ultrix, QNX, OpenVMS, RISC OS, Novell NetWare, DOS and more...
  .
  libcurl is free, thread-safe, IPv6 compatible, feature rich, well supported,
  fast, thoroughly documented and is already used by many known, big and
  successful companies and numerous applications. 

library
  extra-libraries: curl
  build-tools:     hsc2hs
  ghc-options:     -Wall -fwarn-tabs

  build-depends:
    base   == 4.*,
    time   == 1.*

  exposed-modules:
    Network.Curlhs
    Network.Curlhs.Types
    Network.Curlhs.Functions
    Network.Curlhs.FFI.Types
    Network.Curlhs.FFI.Symbols
    Network.Curlhs.FFI.Functions
    Network.Curlhs.FFI.Callbacks

  other-modules:
    Network.Curlhs.TypesH
    Network.Curlhs.FFI.TypesH

